counter<-1
  • Modified function to handle SOM brero prototypes and grid. 
# Function for the correlation check
weighted.correlation <- function(v,w,temp_som){
  print(counter)
  x <- temp_som$parameters$the.grid$coord[,'x'] 
  y <- temp_som$parameters$the.grid$coord[,'y']
  #mean of x will be calculated using the number of instances as weight
  mx <- weighted.mean(x,w)
  my <- weighted.mean(y,w)
  mv <- weighted.mean(v,w)
  numx <- sum(w*(x-mx)*(v-mv))
  denomx <- sqrt(sum(w*(x-mx)^2))*sqrt(sum(w*(v-mv)^2))
  numy <- sum(w*(y-my)*(v-mv))
  denomy <- sqrt(sum(w*(y-my)^2))*sqrt(sum(w*(v-mv)^2))
  #correlation for the two axes
  res <- c(numx/denomx,numy/denomy)
  counter<-counter+1
  return(res)
}

#correlations for all the columns of the codebook

# Relevance of the variables

sigma2 <-  sqrt(apply(FS1_T0_Brero$prototypes,2,
                      function(x,effectif){
                        m<-sum(effectif*(x-weighted.mean(x,effectif))^2)/(sum(effectif)-1)
                        },
                      effectif=tab_num_instances))
